## 1. OpenAI non-streaming (stream=false)

$ curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18317/v1/chat/completions \
    -H 'content-type: application/json' \
    -d '{
      "model": "composer-2.5",
      "stream": false,
      "messages": [ {"role": "user", "content": "Say hi in exactly 3 words."} ]
    }'

{
  "choices": [
    {"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0,
     "message": {"content": "Hi there friend.", "role": "assistant"}}
  ],
  "created": 1783625687,
  "id": "chatcmpl-cd21d3ea-4fae-4da8-8ed0-c51fb4ce36b7",
  "model": "composer-2.5",
  "object": "chat.completion",
  "usage": {
    "completion_tokens": 215,
    "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 0},
    "prompt_tokens": 13080,
    "prompt_tokens_details": {"cached_tokens": 4675},
    "total_tokens": 13295
  }
}

Cursor reports cache_read_tokens = 4675 for the composer-2.5 system prompt
(the exact "warm" value called out in the task brief). Surfaces as
prompt_tokens_details.cached_tokens per OpenAI shape.

## 2. Anthropic non-streaming (stream=false)

$ curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18317/v1/messages \
    -H 'content-type: application/json' \
    -d '{
      "model": "composer-2.5",
      "stream": false,
      "max_tokens": 100,
      "messages": [ {"role": "user", "content": "Say hi in exactly 3 words."} ]
    }'

{
  "content": [{"text": "Hello there friend.", "type": "text"}],
  "id": "msg_0245ad2d-ae85-46a5-bd61-af51934345a6",
  "model": "composer-2.5",
  "role": "assistant",
  "stop_reason": "end_turn",
  "stop_sequence": null,
  "type": "message",
  "usage": {
    "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0,
    "cache_read_input_tokens": 4675,
    "input_tokens": 8405,
    "output_tokens": 115
  }
}

input_tokens = 13080 - 4675 = 8405, matching Anthropic's convention that
input_tokens excludes cached reads. cache_read_input_tokens = 4675.

## 3. OpenAI streaming with stream_options.include_usage=true

$ curl -s -N -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18317/v1/chat/completions \
    -H 'content-type: application/json' \
    -d '{
      "model": "composer-2.5",
      "stream": true,
      "stream_options": {"include_usage": true},
      "messages": [ {"role": "user", "content": "Say hi in exactly 3 words."} ]
    }'

... (role delta, content delta, finish_reason=stop chunk) ...
data: {"choices":[],"created":1783625758,"id":"chatcmpl-c999c911-601b-4688-a1cf-2e74a4117433","model":"composer-2.5","object":"chat.completion.chunk","usage":{"completion_tokens":44,"completion_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":0},"prompt_tokens":13080,"prompt_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":13052},"total_tokens":13124}}

data: [DONE]

Empty `choices` on the trailing chunk + fully populated `usage` — matches
OpenAI's include_usage contract. Cursor's server had warmed the cache further
by this point so cached_tokens climbed to 13052 (near-total hit).

## 4. Anthropic streaming (message_delta usage)

$ curl -s -N -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18317/v1/messages \
    -H 'content-type: application/json' \
    -d '{
      "model": "composer-2.5",
      "stream": true,
      "max_tokens": 100,
      "messages": [ {"role": "user", "content": "Say hi in exactly 3 words."} ]
    }'

... (message_start, content_block_start/delta/stop) ...
event: message_delta
data: {"delta":{"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null},"type":"message_delta","usage":{"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4675,"input_tokens":8405,"output_tokens":234}}

event: message_stop
data: {"type":"message_stop"}

message_delta.usage carries cache_read_input_tokens=4675 alongside
cache_creation_input_tokens=0. input_tokens follows the same
"total minus cache_read" clamp used by non-streaming.

## Summary

- Cursor's server-side cache for composer-2.5 reports cache_read_tokens=4675
  on cold-ish runs and continues to grow as the session progresses.
- cache_write_tokens observed on every request: 0 (Cursor does not accept
  client-directed caching, as noted in the task brief).
- reasoning_tokens observed here: 0 (composer-2.5 non-thinking mode); the
  translator plumbs it through so thinking models will surface non-zero
  values without a code change.

